#: 5ec01b69f80d42979834a8f80b2743ad of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:1
msgid "Module-aware dict of tensors stored as buffers (non-trainable)."
msgstr ""

#: 43cba49d947e4d97a5abd134e5022d7d of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:3
msgid ""
"Use it whenever you need a dict of plain tensors attached to a "
":class:`~torch.nn.Module` — for example integer connectivity "
"``[n_element, n_basis]``, vector point data ``[n_point, D]``, or "
"precomputed quadrature tables — keyed by element type or field name. "
"Tensors registered through :class:`BufferDict` follow the parent module "
"under ``.to(device)`` / ``.float()`` / ``.cuda()``, appear in "
":meth:`~torch.nn.Module.state_dict`, and do not require gradients."
msgstr ""

#: f8b7655d70e1486a9f8659927d34062d of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:11
msgid "Two behaviours go beyond a plain :meth:`~torch.nn.Module.register_buffer`:"
msgstr ""

#: c94c5656e0af42ef876c15bc6d719f1d of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:13
msgid ""
"**Keys that aren't valid Python identifiers** (anything not matching "
"``^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$``, e.g. ``\"123x\"`` or names with dashes) are"
" stored in an internal :class:`~collections.OrderedDict` (:attr:`_data`) "
"instead of being registered as buffers — Python's ``register_buffer`` "
"rejects such names. Their tensors are still moved by :meth:`_apply`, so "
"``.to(device)`` and friends still work; they just don't appear in "
":meth:`~torch.nn.Module.state_dict`."
msgstr ""

#: 7c0e6af2256842cbb74095018a6cdda0 of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:20
msgid ""
"**Buffer ↔ parameter promotion**: :meth:`as_parameter` turns a stored "
"buffer into a trainable :class:`~torch.nn.Parameter` in place, and "
":meth:`as_buffer` reverses it. This lets the same container serve both "
"pure-FEM workflows (everything as buffers) and ML workflows where some "
"fields need gradients (e.g. learnable material parameters)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/nn.rst 88399ce4d0154167bbfe395d6bbb4c48
#: 8ba0536c959d44e48911136148f00d35
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: 774c76427d5140b68b434cfa3688b74e of tensormesh.nn.buffer_dict.BufferDict:26
msgid ""
"Initial key→tensor mapping. Keys matching ``^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$`` "
"are registered as buffers via :meth:`~torch.nn.Module.register_buffer`; "
"the rest are kept in the fallback :attr:`_data` dict. Default: empty."
msgstr ""

