#: 4f4315810967453789f1dcfb2c9edef0 of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:1
msgid "Module-aware list of tensors stored as buffers (non-trainable)."
msgstr ""

#: 098564c021a54e4a8ecb9787c7c724a0 of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:3
msgid ""
"The list analogue of :class:`~tensormesh.nn.BufferDict`. Same motivation:"
" PyTorch ships :class:`torch.nn.ParameterList` and "
":class:`torch.nn.ModuleList` but no list of buffers. :class:`BufferList` "
"provides one — tensors are stored under stringified indices via "
":meth:`~torch.nn.Module.register_buffer`, so they follow ``.to(device)`` "
"and appear in :meth:`~torch.nn.Module.state_dict`."
msgstr ""

#: 9d1bf9dafe3845c7b07c3211c65f89e6 of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:10
msgid ""
"Used inside :class:`~tensormesh.FacetAssembler` to hold the per-element-"
"type boundary-facet masks — for mixed-facet elements like prisms and "
"pyramids, each element type contributes more than one mask tensor (e.g. a"
" triangle-facet mask *and* a quad-facet mask), so a list of buffers per "
"key is the natural shape."
msgstr ""

#: e3d5ca9a20284969a23b56a0ce450f7f of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:16
msgid ""
"Beyond standard list indexing (``int``, ``slice``), :meth:`__getitem__` "
"also accepts a 1D :class:`torch.Tensor` of indices and returns a fresh "
":class:`BufferList` — convenient for gather-style operations."
msgstr ""

#: 0d04c584e9de4c6d810fe7464cbcd08b of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:20
msgid ""
"Like :class:`BufferDict`, individual entries can be promoted to trainable"
" parameters via :meth:`as_parameter` (and demoted back via "
":meth:`as_buffer`)."
msgstr ""

#: acdd8037521d4d5987c22f33eae1578f of tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList:23
msgid "Initial tensors. Default: empty."
msgstr ""

#: dbf40f3d3f1c48fc844eeb83c88895bb of
#: tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList.as_parameter:1
msgid ""
"Promote the buffer at index ``key`` to a trainable "
":class:`torch.nn.Parameter` in place."
msgstr ""

#: 708287d182204cfca695807d6001fde5 of
#: tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList.as_buffer:1
msgid ""
"Demote the parameter at index ``key`` back to a (non-trainable) buffer in"
" place."
msgstr ""

#: 902f0e76e64444ff8cc0d1116866b87f of
#: tensormesh.nn.buffer_list.BufferList.as_buffer:3
msgid ""
"Storage is shared via :meth:`~torch.Tensor.detach`; the result no longer "
"requires grad."
msgstr ""

